<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,812,1269]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,847,872]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Description.</emphasis>
Shell length to 
<quantity box="[527,615,848,872]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="8.4">8.4 mm</quantity>
(up to 
<quantity box="[699,779,847,872]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Powell, A. W. B." box="[937,1083,847,872]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" pagination="49 - 196" refId="ref18651" refString="Powell, A. W. B. (1951) Antarctic and Subantarctic Mollusca: Pelecypoda and Gastropoda collected by the ships of the Discovery Committee during the years 1926 - 1937. Discovery Reports, 26, 49 - 196, pls. 5 - 10." type="journal article" year="1951">Powell 1951</bibRefCitation>
); patelliform, high, moderately thick. Apex rolled, located at posterior fourth of total length. Surface white; sculptured with 35 to 45 strong, radial ribs, and minute pits, arranged in rows. Aperture ovate, interior white, margin crenulated. Slit and septum elongated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,812,1269]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,991,1016]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Remarks.</emphasis>
Five species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lowe" authorityYear="1827" box="[519,650,991,1016]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[519,650,991,1016]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Puncturella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were described / mentioned from the sub-Antarctic and Antarctic waters: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1771)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1771" box="[241,580,1028,1053]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="noachina">
<emphasis box="[241,375,1028,1053]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P. noachina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus, C." box="[392,571,1028,1053]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" pagination="143 - 588" refId="ref17168" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1771) Mantissa Plantarum. Vol. 1. 6. Laurentius Salvius, Stockholm, 143 - 588." type="book chapter" year="1771">Linnaeus, 1771</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1841" box="[594,699,1029,1052]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="conica">
<emphasis box="[594,699,1029,1052]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P. conica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Gould, 1852)" baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[715,1007,1028,1053]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cognata">
<emphasis box="[715,835,1029,1052]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P. cognata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Gould, A. A." box="[852,1000,1028,1053]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" refId="ref16072" refString="Gould, A. A. (1852) Mollusca &amp; Shells. In: United States Exploring Expeditions, 1838, 1839, 1840, 1841, 1842 under the command of Charles Wilkes, U. S. N. Vol. 12. C. Sherman &amp; sons, Philadelphia, xv + 510 pp." type="book" year="1852">Gould, 1852</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Adams, 1866)" baseAuthorityName="Adams" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[1021,1357,1028,1053]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="falklandica">
<emphasis box="[1021,1177,1028,1053]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P. falklandica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Adams, A." box="[1194,1348,1028,1053]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" pagination="207 - 226" refId="ref13671" refString="Adams, A. (1866) Monographs of the genera Cemoria, Cranopsis, Zeidora, Rimula, Emarginula, Scutus &amp; Tugalia. In: Sowerby, G. B. I. (Ed.), Thesaurus Conchyliorum. Vol. 3. Privately published, London, pp. 207 - 226, pls. 10 - 14." type="book chapter" year="1866">Adams, 1866</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Thiele, 1912" authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1912" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="spirigera">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P. spirigera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thiele, J." box="[261,406,1063,1088]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" pagination="183" refId="ref20178" refString="Thiele, J. (1912) Die Antarktischen Schnecken und Muscheln. Deutsche Sudpolar Expedition 1901 - 1903, 13, Zoologie 5 (2), 183 ‾ 285, pls. 11 - 19." type="journal article" year="1912">Thiele, 1912</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. After studying the radula, 
<bibRefCitation author="Powell, A. W. B." box="[715,874,1063,1088]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" pagination="49 - 196" refId="ref18651" refString="Powell, A. W. B. (1951) Antarctic and Subantarctic Mollusca: Pelecypoda and Gastropoda collected by the ships of the Discovery Committee during the years 1926 - 1937. Discovery Reports, 26, 49 - 196, pls. 5 - 10." type="journal article" year="1951">Powell (1951)</bibRefCitation>
concluded that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1771" box="[1054,1186,1063,1088]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="noachina">
<emphasis box="[1054,1186,1063,1088]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P. noachina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1841" box="[1242,1345,1065,1088]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="conica">
<emphasis box="[1242,1345,1065,1088]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P. conica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are two different entities, the former being a boreal species, wrongly previously mentioned from the sub-Antarctic waters. The validity of the other four species deserves further study, due to the discrepant opinions by different authors: 
<bibRefCitation author="Powell, A. W. B." box="[151,310,1172,1197]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" pagination="49 - 196" refId="ref18651" refString="Powell, A. W. B. (1951) Antarctic and Subantarctic Mollusca: Pelecypoda and Gastropoda collected by the ships of the Discovery Committee during the years 1926 - 1937. Discovery Reports, 26, 49 - 196, pls. 5 - 10." type="journal article" year="1951">Powell (1951)</bibRefCitation>
regarded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1841" box="[422,525,1173,1196]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="conica">
<emphasis box="[422,525,1173,1196]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P. conica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Gould" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[538,656,1173,1196]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cognata">
<emphasis box="[538,656,1173,1196]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P. cognata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thiele" authorityYear="1912" box="[710,841,1173,1196]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="spirigera">
<emphasis box="[710,841,1173,1196]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P. spirigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid species, with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Adams" baseAuthorityYear="1866" box="[1092,1246,1172,1197]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="falklandica">
<emphasis box="[1092,1246,1172,1197]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P. falklandica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of the former; alternatively, 
<bibRefCitation author="Reid, D. G. &amp; Osorio, C." box="[444,699,1207,1232]" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" pagination="109 - 146" refId="ref18876" refString="Reid, D. G. &amp; Osorio, C. (2000) The shallow-water marine Mollusca of the Estero Elefantes and Laguna San Rafael, southern Chile. Bulletin of natural History of Museum, London, Zoology, 66 (2), 109 - 146." type="journal article" year="2000">Reid &amp; Osorio (2000)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that “it is possible that only a single species may be involved” among all these taxa, for which they used the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="d'Orbigny" authorityYear="1841" box="[849,951,1245,1268]" class="Gastropoda" family="Fissurellidae" genus="Puncturella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Archaeogastropoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="conica">
<emphasis box="[849,951,1245,1268]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">P. conica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This criterion is followed herein.
</paragraph>
